# Obj Add Tags

Add tags to an object version.

PUT

/

objs

/

{object_id}

/

versions

/

{digest}

/

tags

Obj Add Tags
    
    
    curl --request PUT \
      --url https://api.example.com/objs/{object_id}/versions/{digest}/tags \
      --header 'Authorization: Basic <encoded-value>' \
      --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
      --data '
    {
      "project_id": "<string>",
      "tags": [
        "<string>"
      ]
    }
    '
    
    
    {}

#### Authorizations

HTTPBasicHTTPBearerHTTPBasicHTTPBearer

​

Authorization

string

header

required

Basic authentication header of the form `Basic <encoded-value>`, where `<encoded-value>` is the base64-encoded string `username:password`.

#### Path Parameters

​

object_id

string

required

​

digest

string

required

#### Body

application/json

Request body for adding/removing tags (object_id and digest come from path).

​

project_id

string

required

Example:

`"entity/project"`

​

tags

string[]

required

Example:
    
    
    ["production", "reviewed"]

#### Response

Successful Response

The response is of type `ObjAddTagsRes · object`.

